Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:00:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The professor is back in the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.42,0:00:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.71,0:01:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We will resume the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.53,0:01:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Finishing up with left brain versus right brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.45,0:01:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so fundamental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.21,0:01:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you understand that, then that helps you with forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.43,0:01:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're forgiving somebody whose brain does not work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.47,0:01:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If their brain worked like yours, then you could hate them, but they don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.67,0:01:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.87,0:01:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Run by animal instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.46,0:01:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Run by animal instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire for power, megalomania, having to dominate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.97,0:01:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.07,0:01:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on to perception versus essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.98,0:01:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason it's important, which we'll get to,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.45,0:02:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the other night on TV came the statement made by a very good commentator.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.58,0:02:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In the part of the world, he was on the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, in this side of the world, perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.38,0:02:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.42,0:02:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, in just a couple of words, he encapsulated the entire difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.60,0:02:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pervasive effect of the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.06,0:02:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because perception, which is what he's, the world considers this to be a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.94,0:02:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Opinion has equal value with fact, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.07,0:02:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsity, legally, has the same defense as truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.10,0:02:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Legally.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.57,0:02:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bill of Rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.93,0:02:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bill of Rights is probably unconstitutional, and they'll get rid of it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.13,0:02:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my private little joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.14,0:02:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.95,0:02:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just my opinion, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.63,0:02:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is a distortion, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.44,0:03:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably emotional and reactive, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.51,0:03:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also quite mental.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.73,0:03:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.47,0:03:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So perception, then, is what we see and jump to the conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.89,0:03:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's blogger's land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.65,0:03:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is blogger's land over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.30,0:03:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence is acceptance, awareness, clarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So seeing essence is not really possible until really a relatively high level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.64,0:03:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called the opening of the third eye of the Buddhic body,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.04,0:03:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the third eye opens, and now what you see is essence rather than perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.51,0:03:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes as an intuitive knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.63,0:03:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Intuitive knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.27,0:03:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the Trojan horse, the person with essence knows
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.47,0:03:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not giving you a Trojan horse for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.53,0:03:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You better look inside, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.89,0:04:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in perception says, oh, look at the wonderful Trojan horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.67,0:04:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.11,0:04:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But essence tells you that they're hiding behind religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not doing it because of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.69,0:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion is their cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.95,0:04:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's their Trojan horse, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.55,0:04:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that, you can get away with more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.53,0:04:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So essence, then, is actually sort of automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.22,0:04:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, while we shift from perception to essence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.60,0:04:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to the calibrated levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a means now of discerning essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.02,0:04:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We can actually calibrate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.28,0:04:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the amount of relative truth is compared to an absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.60,0:04:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are seen to be what they are, and not as they appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.04,0:04:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.74,0:04:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're not as they appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.84,0:04:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not as they appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.86,0:04:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the ego projects its motives upon the world, gain or loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.82,0:05:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees it as good and bad, and it projects its value and belief,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore meaning, onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the sage says, there's no point in trying to change the world you see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.68,0:05:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.18,0:05:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The world you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.90,0:05:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's all perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.14,0:05:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you understand the essence of, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.64,0:05:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of human existence, and then you see that the world is perfect the way it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.10,0:05:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,optimum opportunity for karmic merit, optimum opportunity for the undoing of negative merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the optimum environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.03,0:05:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what the Buddha meant when he said, rare it is to be born human.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.22,0:05:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, rarer still to have heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarest of all to have heard of it and then proceed to pursue it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.48,0:05:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.05,0:05:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So the purpose of these classes is to aid and facilitate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.73,0:05:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the pursuit of the condition of enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.05,0:06:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or transcending the ego altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.81,0:06:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the overall purpose of the content of the lecture, I suggest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.05,0:06:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, perception, then, is a projection of motivations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's selective, it's very personal, it's volitional,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's attraction and aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.33,0:06:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, to constantly let go of your attractions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.03,0:06:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and your emotions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.59,0:06:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and let go of your aversions is one very important way to transcend the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.57,0:06:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So let go of your aversions and let go of being glamorized by your attractions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.63,0:06:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to talk about memes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.03,0:06:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence is witnessed, it's impersonal,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.11,0:06:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a revelation, it's a knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.91,0:06:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a recognition, and it often comes sort of intuitively.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.61,0:06:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Intuitively.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I tend to go back and retrack reason a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.04,0:07:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times, a student just skips the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.00,0:07:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and intuitively says what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.32,0:07:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.99,0:07:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Saves herself 13 pages of typewritten stuff to read through.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.09,0:07:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.59,0:07:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes right to the essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.99,0:07:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that influence perception are rather obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.28,0:07:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What's not obvious is the...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.93,0:07:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's now purposeful brainwashing by the media of the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.43,0:07:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It is actually intentional, it is not exactly innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.43,0:07:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite deliberate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.79,0:07:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The deliberate programming of the public via the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.70,0:07:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Reuters has joined into it, and so therefore, academia fell into it quite a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.78,0:07:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The progressive programming of the human mind, my only concern about it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:08:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it's going to injure the capacity of the human mind even further than it already is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.68,0:08:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.00,0:08:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness, of course, is the one we're most familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.24,0:08:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that where your level of consciousness is, is how you see the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.49,0:08:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In a divine state, you see the world as perfect because everything is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Programming is very considerable with today's world, and we'll get to some of the popular memes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The set and the setting, the priorities, this is important, priorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.79,0:08:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason, you know, what I talk about in one of the books there is the processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.82,0:08:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading edge of the ego is the processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.82,0:08:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know which book it is, but it's processing, the processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.65,0:08:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And this processing takes one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.65,0:08:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's reality, there's the world the way it is, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.57,0:08:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.89,0:09:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's processed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.89,0:09:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the information, there's a one ten-thousandth of a second delay
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.92,0:09:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,between the sound of the music and the time you hear the music, let's put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.92,0:09:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, people hear different things, and I recently read a scientific paper
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.34,0:09:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by a doctor named John Medina, who I have to contact and exchange information with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.63,0:09:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's called intentional set, that the mind has...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He says the mind has multiple processors, which I'll agree with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.08,0:09:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but they subsume as one primary processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.08,0:09:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You give that which you value dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.78,0:09:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind has multiple options all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.91,0:09:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happens is certain fields, I call them attractor fields, become more powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.91,0:09:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you then begin to experience and perceive and interpret via predominant intentional set.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual commitment is really an intentional set.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That intentional set then influences the priority of perception with experience in any profession or field.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.16,0:10:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The mature person in the field, the experienced person, has trained their perceptual set,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.19,0:10:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so they don't have to tune around the dial to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.19,0:10:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Their predominant set, for instance, in the airport, the...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.35,0:10:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call that difficult job?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.64,0:10:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A difficult job, controlling all the controller in the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.64,0:10:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, he's got an intentional set that allows him to handle complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you and I tried to go from this bit of da-da-da, this bit of da-da-da, this bit of da-da-da, this bit of da-da-da,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.64,0:10:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you would break down in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.64,0:10:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They have an intentional set that gives them the whole program like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.64,0:10:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual intention then sets a set of priorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:11:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your priorities are to see the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the eyes of forgiveness, through benevolence, through, you know, unconditional love, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.24,0:11:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So spirituality is merely a setting of priorities of these intentional sets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And after a while, it becomes habitual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes habitual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.50,0:11:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Other perceptual influences are obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Age, sex, and gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.88,0:11:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the politicalization of all these things, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.88,0:11:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things have become political now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.88,0:11:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm starting a protest group, a protest thing, calling it Mother Nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's very sexist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.88,0:11:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm calling it Mother Father Nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a protest group, men's protest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.59,0:11:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, it's always pictured as negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.59,0:11:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever watch the weather news?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.59,0:11:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Nature was raging.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.59,0:11:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got bad emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.65,0:11:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only feminine, but she's raging all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.65,0:12:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Nature is raging.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's my protest for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.45,0:12:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.52,0:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the glamour, of course, we know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the seduction has also to do with the meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The instinctual appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.52,0:12:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So left brain, you see, is attracted by different things than right brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.55,0:12:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Left brain, if you remember the guys in the room, if I may be sexist for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The guys in the room, fight, fight, fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.55,0:12:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody runs from the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.55,0:12:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight, fight, fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.09,0:12:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight, fight, fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.09,0:12:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.09,0:12:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.09,0:12:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest excitement of everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.72,0:12:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,New kid in town, there's a big fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.72,0:12:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight, fight, fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be in those fights all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.59,0:12:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I never turned down a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.78,0:12:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time you move to a new class, there's the tough guy in the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.78,0:12:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly comes the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.78,0:12:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I would never turn down the challenge, even though I knew I was going to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.78,0:12:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just scrap like hell as I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.78,0:13:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd get beat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.84,0:13:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was one of the guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I never turned down a challenge just because you were going to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.96,0:13:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the meaning of the glamorization of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Instinctual appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They were appealing to my left brain animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.96,0:13:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior experience, expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.96,0:13:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see all these things that influence perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.96,0:13:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you say perception is reality, you're talking about a very unsubstantial.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all the influences.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.24,0:13:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Your personal needs will exaggerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.24,0:13:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.24,0:13:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How it's presented.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.24,0:13:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.24,0:13:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At the political viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensual appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.24,0:13:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's symbolism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How it's framed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The degree of narcissism versus degree of spiritual commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.24,0:13:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.24,0:13:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to see how narcissism is what the enemy is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.24,0:13:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We think it's Islamic totalitarianism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.24,0:14:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We think it's atheists and secularists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.85,0:14:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And we think it's anti-Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.85,0:14:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever we might think it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.85,0:14:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find that we only have one critter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.85,0:14:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we expose him and take off his sheep's clothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.85,0:14:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find narcissism is at the core of all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.85,0:14:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Core is at the what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.14,0:14:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,For the good of your spirit, I'm going to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.14,0:14:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll go to heaven, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.14,0:14:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.14,0:14:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And it becomes elaborated in the professorial level in current academia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.24,0:14:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.27,0:14:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Alternate viewpoints of hating people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.36,0:14:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,People get very upset because despite their best intention to be forgiving,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.36,0:14:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they still get mad and indignant, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.36,0:14:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some other ways you can look at the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.97,0:14:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say, well, it's sort of a sad mistake, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.97,0:14:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say it's sort of naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.97,0:15:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of the passion for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.97,0:15:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, if you never cared enough to get mad and hate somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.97,0:15:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you probably haven't got enough energy to reach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.97,0:15:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to reach enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.97,0:15:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to care enough about life, a passion for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see people easily duped and misled,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how easily they're programmed and brainwashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's now done systematically.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.32,0:15:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that people are run by karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy fields that you inherit as you come into the body are your own,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.32,0:15:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you have certain proclivities,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.61,0:15:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,certain attractions and certain aversions,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.61,0:15:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and certain agreements also,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.61,0:15:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which you've forgotten about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.61,0:15:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you incarnate, you forget all that went before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.64,0:15:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it isn't until you leave the body that you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.03,0:15:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so, karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.57,0:15:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignorance, of course, as everyone said,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.57,0:15:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say it's ignorance of how the ego itself is constructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.57,0:16:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Many mentally ill people are high up in the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.57,0:16:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They give lectures at universities now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.57,0:16:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They have conspiracy theories, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.57,0:16:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatchamacallit never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.11,0:16:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The, uh, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.11,0:16:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Holocaust never happened, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, they're obviously delusional.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.24,0:16:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when I was younger, we put them in hospitals and treated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.27,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't appoint them as professors
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and they used the taxpayer's money to entertain the troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Politically correct paranoid delusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.48,0:16:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Conspiracy theories calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.48,0:16:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they're on one of the charts coming up later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.55,0:16:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, everybody I ever met who had a conspiracy theory
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.55,0:16:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was suffering from a paranoid condition, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.64,0:16:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh, I think I told you about a couple of them years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.44,0:16:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The FBI was always tapping her phone and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.44,0:16:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, anyway, so people are mentally ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.44,0:17:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, it's amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.44,0:17:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the naivete of the public about mental illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That always surprised me as a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.44,0:17:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I would talk to somebody so deranged that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they couldn't put two sentences together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.44,0:17:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so obvious they were mentally ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.44,0:17:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And people are treating them as though they were a normal person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.44,0:17:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and only screwed up, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.44,0:17:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, really, they couldn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.44,0:17:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.44,0:17:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, the leaders,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.54,0:17:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,practically every dictator calibrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.54,0:17:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, you know, 90 to 180 in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.57,0:17:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, they're all suffering from grandiose megalomania.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.57,0:17:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And the condition they have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.67,0:17:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is what we used to treat with penicillin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.67,0:17:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called cerebral syphilis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.67,0:17:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all ended up with granite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.67,0:17:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We had all kinds of Jesuses and Napoleons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.67,0:17:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.89,0:17:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you can be the leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.99,0:17:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Leader of a great country.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.99,0:17:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get up there and you talk about the Holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.99,0:17:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, it's documented.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.99,0:17:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see it on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.01,0:18:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that may be funny because, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.01,0:18:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,after World War II, as a psychiatrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to interview many Holocaust survivors
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.01,0:18:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because they got compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.01,0:18:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who had been, uh, uh, injured by it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.01,0:18:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, PTSD, various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,With the government, the...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was the German government,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.01,0:18:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, those who had been in concentration camps
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.17,0:18:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,were entitled to compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.17,0:18:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I had the chance to interview many hundreds of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, the doctor had to give a report,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.20,0:18:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, you know, verifying the person's experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.20,0:18:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So not only is it documented in the world history,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.20,0:18:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but I personally interviewed many
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.20,0:18:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of them as well as their families.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, thousands of people were person...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.20,0:18:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,had a personal experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.20,0:18:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's a guy getting up telling you that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.20,0:18:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, it's all a Jewish plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.20,0:18:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.20,0:18:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Medically ill people now run the world, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.20,0:18:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's also genetic defects.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.48,0:18:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's degrees of vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.48,0:19:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy that's dominating.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, most of these people are extremely infantile
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.64,0:19:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They are actually quite atavistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.64,0:19:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Freud postulated
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.64,0:19:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,two opposing primary energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.64,0:19:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, eros versus thanatos.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.64,0:19:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Eros is the energy of life, commitment to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.64,0:19:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,desire for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And thanatos is deep buried
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.64,0:19:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the depths of the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the attraction to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.64,0:19:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The death and the glamour of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.64,0:19:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day you can watch
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,people climb a, uh, high mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,where, uh, 150 people have died already.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.71,0:19:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can't wait to put their clompons on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.71,0:19:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and get up there where 150 people
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.71,0:19:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,have just died.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.03,0:19:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Including experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.03,0:19:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Expert guides die, right,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.03,0:19:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and left the same as everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.03,0:19:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't wait to get up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.03,0:19:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like thanatos.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.03,0:19:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The flirting with death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.03,0:19:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How fast can you make it around
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.03,0:19:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a gravel road on your motorcycle?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.03,0:19:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember two guys betting each other
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.03,0:20:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,if they could make it at 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.03,0:20:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, if you're wrong, you died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.03,0:20:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all, uh, over a bottle of beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.35,0:20:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You make it, I'll buy you beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.35,0:20:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't make it, you buy me a beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.69,0:20:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good bet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.69,0:20:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you lose it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.69,0:20:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to pay them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.11,0:20:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction to death
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.11,0:20:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and flirting with death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.11,0:20:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I always warn people,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.11,0:20:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, don't flirt with death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.11,0:20:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.11,0:20:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.11,0:20:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a, a rejection
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.11,0:20:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the, um, gift of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.11,0:20:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rejecting the, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.36,0:20:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the value of the gift of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.36,0:20:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't do that with your dollar bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.36,0:20:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw them over, you know, with a parachute on them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.36,0:20:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and see if they'll make it or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.36,0:20:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.75,0:20:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But you do it with your human body
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.75,0:20:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for a cheap thrill.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.75,0:20:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to turn down the cheap thrill
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.75,0:21:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of endangering your life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.75,0:21:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's social coercion, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.84,0:21:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, which is very strong in universities.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.84,0:21:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative emotional states.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.84,0:21:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,People tend to compartmentalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.94,0:21:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll believe a whole thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.94,0:21:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's compartmentalized personalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.94,0:21:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,personality disorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.94,0:21:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissistic megalomania
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.94,0:21:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is like the leader of Iran
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.94,0:21:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and various people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.94,0:21:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are people
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.94,0:21:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,who have unrecognized psychosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.94,0:21:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and many of them are in the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get above intention
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.94,0:21:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is just be crazy as all get out
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or say crazy things,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.94,0:21:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're ready while you're on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.94,0:21:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,have an impulse disorder,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.94,0:21:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and this shows up before age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.94,0:21:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Unable to hold back an impulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.94,0:21:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows up in infants.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.77,0:21:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also the basis of psychopathic personality
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.77,0:21:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,who's also unable to control their impulses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.77,0:22:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So the foolishness of putting a person away
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.77,0:22:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for one deed and giving them no,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, short term.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.16,0:22:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Various commentators on TV
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.16,0:22:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,get indignant about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.16,0:22:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Some guy has raped a couple little kids
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.16,0:22:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and all, and he gets 30 days in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.16,0:22:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.16,0:22:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And the idea is,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.16,0:22:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,well, he'll get help
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.22,0:22:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if we let him out of jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.22,0:22:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, that's the absolute truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.22,0:22:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I treated a lot of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.22,0:22:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.22,0:22:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for maybe one occurrence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.22,0:22:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of pedophilia or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them admitted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.22,0:22:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that they had molested hundreds,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.22,0:22:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds, at least once a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.28,0:22:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 50 kids a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.28,0:22:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.28,0:22:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,over a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.28,0:22:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,over 10 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.28,0:22:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,500 kids, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.89,0:22:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Those that were honest with me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.89,0:22:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a little older said,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.89,0:22:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's probably been a thousand stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.40,0:22:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you arrest them for one,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.40,0:22:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,give them 10 days in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.40,0:22:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because now he's going to get treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.40,0:22:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.40,0:22:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.40,0:22:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The average pedophiliac is arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.40,0:23:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is molested hundreds and hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.40,0:23:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.40,0:23:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're driven by compulsion
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.40,0:23:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of lack of education,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.40,0:23:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,psychopathic conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.40,0:23:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People are purposely misinformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.40,0:23:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are delusional.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.40,0:23:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.40,0:23:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.40,0:23:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the nutty professors.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.40,0:23:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are subcultures now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.40,0:23:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who have become delusional,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.40,0:23:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll get to them later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.47,0:23:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Lack of spiritual evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.47,0:23:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.47,0:23:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is the predominant thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.47,0:23:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's regression
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and degeneration.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.47,0:23:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What many intellectual elitists think
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.47,0:23:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is evolutionary is actually degenerative,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.47,0:23:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's regression and degeneration,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.47,0:23:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,not evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.47,0:23:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.24,0:23:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.24,0:23:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that these things influence everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.24,0:23:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,allows for acceptance,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.24,0:23:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,limitation of the human condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.24,0:23:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest limitation is the evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.52,0:23:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of human consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.52,0:23:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't expect people to be,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.52,0:23:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,see things at level 700
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.52,0:24:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're still struggling to get up to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.44,0:24:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You arrive at an understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.44,0:24:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a tolerance,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.44,0:24:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and a patience,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.44,0:24:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain forbearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.44,0:24:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.44,0:24:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We all say that mistakes are inevitable in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.44,0:24:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willingness to forgive ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.44,0:24:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of heaping ashes on your head
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.57,0:24:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that you made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.57,0:24:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.57,0:24:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.57,0:24:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.57,0:24:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.57,0:24:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the processor in the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.57,0:24:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is not that good at prioritizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.57,0:24:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.57,0:24:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,what it prioritizes is tendencies
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.57,0:24:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but not certainties.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.57,0:24:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're dealing with is likelihoods.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.57,0:24:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A spiritually committed person
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.18,0:24:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,has the likelihood 90% of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.18,0:24:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll try to find a way
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.18,0:24:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the person
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.18,0:24:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.18,0:24:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But 10% of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.18,0:24:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.18,0:24:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll hate the SOB.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.18,0:24:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.56,0:24:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can't forgive them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.56,0:24:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then you gotta forgive yourself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.56,0:24:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiving others doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.56,0:25:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then forgive yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.56,0:25:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're unable to forgive them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.56,0:25:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the way you see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.56,0:25:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why you ask the Holy Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.56,0:25:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.56,0:25:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Please recontextualize this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.56,0:25:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so I see it in a different light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.56,0:25:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See it in a different light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.56,0:25:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.92,0:25:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we'll move on to the next thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.27,0:25:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We never did the great scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.27,0:25:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in any of the books we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.27,0:25:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We did a lot of,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.27,0:25:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we did scientific theories
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.27,0:25:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.27,0:25:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're talking today about truth versus reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.36,0:25:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.36,0:25:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason is very respectable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.36,0:25:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that the great scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.36,0:25:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all calibrate about the same
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.36,0:25:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as the great books of the western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.65,0:25:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.65,0:25:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s is the domain of logic and reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.65,0:25:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Of mathematics,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.65,0:25:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of very erudite science.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.65,0:25:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.65,0:25:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle, Sir Francis Bacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.65,0:25:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,David Bohm calibrates a little higher
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.81,0:25:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,than most of them at 505.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.81,0:26:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the enfolded and unfolded universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.81,0:26:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Niels Bohr.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.88,0:26:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the great names.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.88,0:26:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Copernicus, Charles Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.88,0:26:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eddington, Thomas Edison.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.07,0:26:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Edison's 490.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.07,0:26:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.07,0:26:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a great genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.07,0:26:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,See, people envy America.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.07,0:26:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what America is?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.07,0:26:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,America is the product of these people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.07,0:26:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Edison in one discovery of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.07,0:26:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,created more wealth
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.23,0:26:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,than the whole income of other countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.23,0:26:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.23,0:26:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.23,0:26:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Already created great wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.23,0:26:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the computer world, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.23,0:26:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great creativity then
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.32,0:26:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,people envy America's great wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.32,0:26:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the source of its great wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.32,0:26:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.32,0:26:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The inspiration of people like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.32,0:26:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, Albert Einstein at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.32,0:26:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Euclid.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.32,0:26:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Michael Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.32,0:27:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Alexander Fleming.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.36,0:27:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigmund Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.36,0:27:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was my great grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.03,0:27:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I already explained that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.03,0:27:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My analyst was Lionel Lovesey,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.03,0:27:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,whose analyst was Cardiner,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.03,0:27:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,whose analyst was Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.03,0:27:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So Freud is my great grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.03,0:27:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychoanalytically speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.03,0:27:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.16,0:27:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Galen and Galileo.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.67,0:27:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Galvani.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.67,0:27:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephen Hawking.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.67,0:27:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Alive today.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.67,0:27:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,499.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.31,0:27:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Werner Eisenberg,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.31,0:27:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who really changed the world a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.31,0:27:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippocrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.31,0:27:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Huxley.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.31,0:27:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jenner.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.31,0:27:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The vaccination.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.31,0:27:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, most of us in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.31,0:27:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't even be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.31,0:27:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We all got vaccinated as kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.31,0:27:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we would have, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.31,0:27:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,probably not made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.31,0:27:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Kekul,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.31,0:27:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who got an insight into the carbon molecule
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.31,0:27:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.31,0:27:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the snake swallowing its own tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.31,0:27:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And he got the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.60,0:27:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ernst Mach.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.60,0:27:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Malthus.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.60,0:27:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,James Maxwell.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.60,0:28:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the great names of Sir Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.60,0:28:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian dimension is what dominates us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.60,0:28:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian dimension calibrates in the mid-400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.60,0:28:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but its inventor was at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.85,0:28:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He created the differential calculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.85,0:28:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.85,0:28:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Sir Isaac Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.85,0:28:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a great contribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.85,0:28:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.85,0:28:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.85,0:28:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it is also a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.40,0:28:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is the world of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.40,0:28:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of modern science.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.40,0:28:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.40,0:28:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oot Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.40,0:28:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,well, science is in the mid, like, 460,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.40,0:28:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe even as high as 480.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.43,0:28:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton calibrated 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.43,0:28:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.43,0:28:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrated higher than his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.43,0:28:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, a person can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.43,0:28:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A person calibrates at about the same level as their work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.56,0:28:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.56,0:28:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,these great scientists with these great minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.56,0:28:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he was intensely spiritual, religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.75,0:28:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.75,0:29:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of the great scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.75,0:29:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,were themselves very spiritual and very religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.75,0:29:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So Sir Isaac Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.75,0:29:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,although he declared the importance of reason and logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.91,0:29:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,himself was very spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.91,0:29:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Louis Pasteur, Max Planck,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.91,0:29:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,look at all the great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.91,0:29:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Semmelweis, childbirth fever,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.91,0:29:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the infection is due to germs,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.94,0:29:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles Steinmetz,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.94,0:29:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Teilhard de Chardin, Pierre,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.94,0:29:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and Ludwig Wittgenstein, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.10,0:29:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are all in the mid 400s
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.10,0:29:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to the very high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.10,0:29:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There you have erudition,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.39,0:29:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual erudition.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.39,0:29:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where the universities used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.39,0:29:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The universities used to be in this range.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.39,0:29:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The universities' academia was in the range
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.39,0:29:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.80,0:30:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectual excellence, elegance,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.80,0:30:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the rules of logic, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.24,0:30:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the great scientists who shaped our,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.24,0:30:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course they are all greatly honored,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.24,0:30:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see what they created.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.24,0:30:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What came out of their creation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.24,0:30:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is today's world,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.24,0:30:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and what the world envies
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.44,0:30:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence of their genius
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.44,0:30:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and their productivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.44,0:30:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Move on next, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.44,0:30:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.59,0:30:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, can we get it on?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.59,0:30:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.78,0:30:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just went through what is integrous,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.78,0:30:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what calibrates high,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.78,0:30:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and what has really been beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.78,0:30:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we have to stop the lecture?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.78,0:30:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.54,0:30:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, these are,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.11,0:30:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what the commentators are saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.11,0:30:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is you can't tell truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.11,0:31:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and one of the reasons you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.11,0:31:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is because the common belief now
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.11,0:31:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it doesn't matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.11,0:31:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that falsehood is just as true as truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.24,0:31:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the academic left at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.33,0:31:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It represents itself as aphorism,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.33,0:31:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and we should give favoritism
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.33,0:31:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to various groups, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.33,0:31:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anarchism and atheism.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.33,0:31:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I say
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.33,0:31:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel Dennett's newest book,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.33,0:31:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,his idea is that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.40,0:31:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all religion and philosophy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.40,0:31:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and spirituality is fictional,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.40,0:31:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the professors should get together
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.40,0:31:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and start a revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.40,0:31:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to free man from this ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.04,0:31:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.04,0:31:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So in as much as they calibrate around 85,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.04,0:31:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see how we're going to get liberated.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.04,0:31:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to get liberated from 465
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.04,0:31:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and move to 165.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.20,0:31:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.39,0:31:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Central to the decline of the universities,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.39,0:31:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you do the upper universities
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.39,0:31:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,years ago and now,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.39,0:32:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it makes you feel sick,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.39,0:32:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if you're pouring out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.39,0:32:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of money for tuition,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.39,0:32:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the thinking this,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.39,0:32:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic thinking this of Marcuse
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.39,0:32:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,has infected, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.39,0:32:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,like the universities
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.39,0:32:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought them all down.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.39,0:32:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.39,0:32:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's represented by a deconstructionism.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.39,0:32:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, integrity is demonized, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.39,0:32:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And they brought it down
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.39,0:32:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to dialectical materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.39,0:32:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dixie Chicks who hit the front,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.39,0:32:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the page of the New York Time,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.39,0:32:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Time magazine at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.73,0:32:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The unjustified the means is 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.89,0:32:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course here's the real dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.05,0:32:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,epistemologic relativism,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.05,0:32:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll get to later,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.05,0:32:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the Pope and I agree completely
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.05,0:32:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is the undermining
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.05,0:32:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of our world as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.05,0:32:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Eugenics was popular for a while
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.05,0:32:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with fascism.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.05,0:32:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Secular fascism is 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.08,0:33:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Theocratic fascism is even less, 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.08,0:33:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Islamic militant fascism is 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.53,0:33:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Feminist politics, about which I protested,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.53,0:33:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,mother-father nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.71,0:33:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it emerges as mother-father God, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.09,0:33:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, this is not an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.09,0:33:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.09,0:33:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity is non-linear, beyond gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.51,0:33:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pronoun, he or she,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.51,0:33:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you're talking about biology.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.51,0:33:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about protoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.51,0:33:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God is not protoplasm
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.51,0:33:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or limited to gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.51,0:33:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.51,0:33:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,To say he, she, God
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.10,0:33:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is worse than saying he, God,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.10,0:33:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because now you've double genderized it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.10,0:33:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,into some kind of a hermaphroditic bazaar.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.48,0:33:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine a he, she, God,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.57,0:33:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,two sexes fused together?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.57,0:33:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.73,0:33:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why sexism,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.73,0:34:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we had a lot of them in America,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.83,0:34:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in lectures before,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.83,0:34:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,come up and ask about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.83,0:34:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,why God's called he.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.83,0:34:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, ask them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.83,0:34:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.21,0:34:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.47,0:34:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice in our minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.32,0:34:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we pray to thee, O God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.32,0:34:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't pray to he, O God,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.32,0:34:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or she, O God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.32,0:34:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thee, O Lord, do I worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.32,0:34:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thee.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.32,0:34:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thee is a special word.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.48,0:34:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.48,0:34:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is non-linear
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.52,0:34:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,could hardly have gender,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.52,0:34:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because gender is the description
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.52,0:34:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of separate and linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.52,0:34:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.96,0:34:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, free speech in the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.73,0:34:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as of June is at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.96,0:34:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech in the world in which I grew up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.96,0:34:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.96,0:34:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.99,0:34:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You could disagree,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.99,0:34:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but you didn't vilify.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.99,0:34:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You could disagree,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.99,0:34:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but you didn't vilify.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.99,0:35:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, free speech during the Second World War,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.99,0:35:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the great generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.99,0:35:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The world they lived in,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.99,0:35:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the great generation,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.99,0:35:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is different than the world we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.99,0:35:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.99,0:35:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What your parents grew up in
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.28,0:35:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the world that you grew up in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.98,0:35:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get away with that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.98,0:35:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you would never get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.98,0:35:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world I grew up in,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.98,0:35:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,people would not get away with
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.98,0:35:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the things they say nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.98,0:35:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd jerk them right off the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.98,0:35:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that Major Bo's amateur arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.98,0:35:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It even had a hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.98,0:35:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you came out with something bizarre,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.98,0:35:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,stupid or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.98,0:35:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the hook went out
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.98,0:35:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and they pulled you off the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.98,0:35:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Major Bo's, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.98,0:35:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hate at 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.14,0:35:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We said,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.14,0:35:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the last slide tried to show you ways
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.14,0:35:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoid hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.14,0:35:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That you should just indulge yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.14,0:35:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with no morality or ethics is at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.14,0:36:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Iconoclasm is the destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.14,0:36:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of all belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.14,0:36:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Leads to irresponsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.14,0:36:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And you notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.14,0:36:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when you call a thing an ism,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.14,0:36:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it drops.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.14,0:36:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It drops.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.68,0:36:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one thing to be Catholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.68,0:36:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's another thing to go for Catholicism.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.68,0:36:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because then it becomes a belief system,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.68,0:36:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,takes on political meanings,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.68,0:36:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it loses its essential truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.68,0:36:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So libertarian,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.64,0:36:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,see liberty is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.64,0:36:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Libertarianism is another thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.64,0:36:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the differentiation?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.64,0:36:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral equivalency is justification.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.76,0:36:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really two wrongs make a right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.76,0:36:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really two wrongs make a right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.76,0:36:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The New York Times security breach
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.76,0:36:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,recently calibrated at 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.76,0:36:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.76,0:36:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it was their own messianic narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.92,0:36:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,For the good of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.24,0:37:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we will transcend the survival
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.24,0:37:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of all you peons out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.24,0:37:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to hang with that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.50,0:37:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,until somebody threatens to throw up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.50,0:37:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The New York Times building.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.50,0:37:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will see them switch quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.79,0:37:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Nihilism is no truth to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.79,0:37:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nutty professors, et cetera, 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.95,0:37:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Passivism, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.95,0:37:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that's an ism.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.95,0:37:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Passivism very often leads to defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.95,0:37:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the politicalization of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.95,0:37:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,into an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.36,0:37:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which relies on force rather than power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.36,0:37:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The question authority bumper.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.36,0:37:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When that first appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.36,0:37:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't understand what the hell that meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.36,0:37:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bumper sticker.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.81,0:37:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a question authority on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.97,0:37:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's part of this whole
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.97,0:37:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,nutty professor world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.77,0:37:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I would respect authority
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.77,0:37:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than question it, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.77,0:38:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would find out for myself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.77,0:38:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,by what virtue are the authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.77,0:38:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So calibrating levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.77,0:38:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you what is the intrinsic authority from,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.77,0:38:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the level from which they speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.77,0:38:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which doesn't depend on opinion,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.77,0:38:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't depend on propaganda,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.77,0:38:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't depend on brainwashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.80,0:38:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the intrinsic energy of the essence?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.84,0:38:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.00,0:38:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So philosophic theories are,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.00,0:38:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here's where academia has hit the skids.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.00,0:38:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't know it's hit the skids,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.00,0:38:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but it has badly hit the skids
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.00,0:38:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate academia
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.00,0:38:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,during, let's say, my generation,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.00,0:38:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you calibrate it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.00,0:38:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not even in the same range.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.00,0:38:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So here are the sophistries
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.22,0:38:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which academia tends to worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.22,0:38:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Chomsky, they go in,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.22,0:38:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they just think it's higher than Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.22,0:38:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and higher than,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.22,0:39:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had people send me that,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.18,0:39:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,he's higher than Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.18,0:39:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and higher than Dalai Lama.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.18,0:39:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the very famous,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.08,0:39:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,which a lot of the people you see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.08,0:39:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,parrot all this political garbage,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.08,0:39:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and they don't even know where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.08,0:39:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.08,0:39:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think it's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.08,0:39:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then study these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.08,0:39:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and Foucault, Edmund Husserl,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.08,0:39:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Kristeva, Fritz Kuhn, Jacques Lacan,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.08,0:39:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Lyotard, Herbert Marcuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.33,0:39:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the one who brought down American universities
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.33,0:39:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to the level it's at.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.33,0:39:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,More strongly,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.52,0:39:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if they were going to be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.52,0:39:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they would come out at 135,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.52,0:39:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you follow their line of reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.52,0:39:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they should come out at 135,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.52,0:39:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're fudging to come out at 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.96,0:39:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Carol Popper is the philosopher
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.72,0:40:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,followed by a multi-billionaire
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.72,0:40:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who funds every anti-American energy out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.72,0:40:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and this was his philosophic teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.72,0:40:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's easy to forgive him
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.72,0:40:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was brainwashed at 185,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.72,0:40:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and he thinks this is his truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.98,0:40:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bertrand Russell, Jean Sartre, existentialists,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.98,0:40:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole idea that life is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.98,0:40:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And in our more current world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.98,0:40:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Gore Vidal and Howard Zinn, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.98,0:40:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we'll find out in subsequent chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.98,0:40:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How much more time we got?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.98,0:40:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Five more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.98,0:40:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.98,0:40:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Next chart, quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.04,0:40:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Current memes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.04,0:40:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this will give you a step to get excited over lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.55,0:40:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.55,0:40:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Shepard Smith said that from the Middle East.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.55,0:40:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He said,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.55,0:40:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In this world, perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.55,0:40:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.58,0:41:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say all these professors who tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.74,0:41:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that falsehood is the equivalent of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.74,0:41:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the essence of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.74,0:41:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't mind getting paid with counterfeit money then,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.77,0:41:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,would they?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.12,0:41:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't matter if their check is good
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.12,0:41:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or not, because that's only a point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.68,0:41:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If one man's terrorist is another man's freedom fighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.48,0:41:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then he doesn't mind if we pay him in bogus bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.48,0:41:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is no core reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.58,0:41:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is no such thing as truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.58,0:41:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if falsehood is equal to truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.58,0:41:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,then why should they complain
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.58,0:41:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if I pay them in counterfeit money?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.58,0:41:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you'll see them put their money where their mouth is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.57,0:41:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.57,0:41:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not really believe in that,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.57,0:41:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because all the nutty professors get big money for their lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.64,0:41:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,University of Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.79,0:41:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Holocaust never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.79,0:42:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.79,0:42:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you get big money for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.59,0:42:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The alliance, you know, in contrast to the ACLU,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.59,0:42:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where they went.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.65,0:42:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was ashamed to put them up, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.77,0:42:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can understand why the ACLU calibrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.77,0:42:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.77,0:42:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.77,0:42:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it's 60 or something now.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.77,0:42:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Its founder, George Baldwin, himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.77,0:42:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was a communist sympathizer and an atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.80,0:42:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,agnostic, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.84,0:42:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's the one that set up the Scopes trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.84,0:42:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scopes trial was completely fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.84,0:42:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all manufactured.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.84,0:42:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no actual issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.84,0:42:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They manufactured it in order to get publicity,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.09,0:42:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and also get publicity for the small town at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.12,0:42:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But the founder of the ACLU,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.12,0:42:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of signaled where it was going to end up over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.12,0:42:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look up the books on the ACLU,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.12,0:42:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll see that that's where it was founded.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.12,0:43:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's atheistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.12,0:43:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's secular.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.12,0:43:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates God.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.12,0:43:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.12,0:43:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's always challenging everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.12,0:43:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's challenging everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.12,0:43:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's an actual one that defends freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.12,0:43:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,called Alliance Defense Fund.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.12,0:43:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it's at 480.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.12,0:43:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.12,0:43:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send your donation to 180 or 480.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.12,0:43:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's tact-deductible either way, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.12,0:43:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send them a bum check,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.12,0:43:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,if there's no difference between reality and bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.32,0:43:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to make a donation to the ACLU,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.32,0:43:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course it's going to be a bum check,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.32,0:43:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm sure they won't complain,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.32,0:43:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because if falsehood is equal to truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.32,0:43:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then why would they complain?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.67,0:43:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Castro was very much in the news in the 90s.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.67,0:43:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have one man's freedom fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.67,0:43:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this is moral equivalence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.67,0:43:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the basis of error.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.67,0:43:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A terrorist is not the same as a freedom fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.70,0:43:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A terrorist calibrates at 90, around in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.70,0:44:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And a freedom fighter is usually a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.15,0:44:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to see a picture of a real hero at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.15,0:44:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of this, we're going to give you a picture
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.15,0:44:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of what a real hero really looks like and feels like,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.15,0:44:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so you get the essence of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.15,0:44:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is not Kei Guevara.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.15,0:44:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't so cutesy to wear 90 Energy T-shirts around.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.15,0:44:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.18,0:44:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the university you can do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.18,0:44:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The best they can do is the humanities at 235.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.18,0:44:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They vacated the mid-400s as a source of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.18,0:44:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The best you got is 235, you know, being socially helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.18,0:44:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ideologues, as I said, calibrated 185.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.18,0:44:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.18,0:44:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they confused the hypothetical with the real.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.18,0:44:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,An intellectual construct is not the same as reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.50,0:44:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.92,0:44:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for so-called free speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.92,0:44:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, we got 10 liners to be shot down over the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.92,0:45:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows a confusion between reality and an ideologue.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.92,0:45:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He believes that until his ass is on the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.92,0:45:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I'll tell you how quick he becomes a realist.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.92,0:45:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw him during the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.92,0:45:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave up all that crap in a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.92,0:45:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And they became very, very democratic.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.92,0:45:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew a guy who was a Marxist, you know, in the service.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.92,0:45:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He was an oddity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.92,0:45:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's amazing, when the bullets started,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.92,0:45:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he suddenly became a great American.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.92,0:45:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you'll see, here's the undermining of academia.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.20,0:45:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what's called intellectual narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.20,0:45:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The narcissism of thinking this
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.20,0:45:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ability to put together something that sounds pseudo-persuasive,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.20,0:45:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Marcuse and the relativists.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.20,0:45:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is intellectual narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.49,0:45:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel Danette.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.78,0:45:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We should get rid of all faith, religion, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.00,0:45:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and free the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.00,0:45:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He sounds like Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.00,0:45:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Free the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.00,0:46:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Opium, you know, religion is the opium of the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.00,0:46:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is what he's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.00,0:46:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is his own intellectual narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.00,0:46:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it in skepticism as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.13,0:46:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The skeptic says you cannot,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.13,0:46:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind, you cannot arrive at truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.13,0:46:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And I agree with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.13,0:46:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They then will go on and proceed and give you a big long argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.13,0:46:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which they believe in,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.13,0:46:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which, of course, they have faith in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.13,0:46:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they just got through knocking faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.13,0:46:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but they have faith in their own argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.13,0:46:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so they negate their own argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.13,0:46:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligent design seems to me a nice way out
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.13,0:46:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Scopes dilemma,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.13,0:46:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,religion versus science.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.13,0:46:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But neither side will take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.13,0:46:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious, the intelligence of design,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.13,0:46:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if you've ever watched under a name,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.13,0:46:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a nature film on underwater life,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.13,0:46:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the incredible intelligence of the octopus
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.13,0:46:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as it changes color to match, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.13,0:46:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to quit in three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.13,0:47:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Justification is,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.13,0:47:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you see what the competition in the world is for besides oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.13,0:47:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.13,0:47:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what all the wars are about.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.13,0:47:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.13,0:47:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A whole country could stop having its citizens bombed and killed
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.80,0:47:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by returning two people that they kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.80,0:47:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.72,0:47:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't returned them yet, I don't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.33,0:47:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can blame the other side for bombing you,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.93,0:47:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you were the one that pushed the bomb button.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.93,0:47:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you got the moral high ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.93,0:47:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and, of course, the Middle East right now
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.93,0:47:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is the moral high ground struggle capital of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.93,0:47:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for moral superiority.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.93,0:47:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nasrallah, currently,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.92,0:47:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,North Korean leader, his name I can't remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.12,0:47:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he's about 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.12,0:47:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One-worldism is another fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.18,0:47:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People of conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.60,0:47:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how smug that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.60,0:47:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People of conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.60,0:48:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're a person of conscience?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.60,0:48:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly, gee whiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.60,0:48:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.23,0:48:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in the war, if you don't want to kill anybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.23,0:48:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you become a conscientious objector.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.64,0:48:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't desert the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.64,0:48:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,become a turncoat,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.64,0:48:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin attacking your country.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.64,0:48:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You just stay, you don't want to kill anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.28,0:48:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they give you a desk job.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.76,0:48:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you a radio operator?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.76,0:48:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to always be killing somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.76,0:48:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself was within conscientious objector,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.89,0:48:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but I never had, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.89,0:48:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was put in a position where I'd have to kill somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.89,0:48:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But the guys on the ship, if I said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.89,0:48:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they had another guy on the 20-calibrand aircraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.89,0:48:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I said to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.89,0:48:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I just ain't got an enemy to kill the guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.89,0:48:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,even if he is a son of a bitch of a Jap,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.89,0:48:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he would have said, okay, oh, Shorty,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.89,0:48:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,my name was Shorty in the service,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.89,0:48:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, Shorty, I'll take the 20 million,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.89,0:48:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,don't bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.89,0:48:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, it was an okay thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.89,0:48:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't have to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.89,0:48:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,if you said, I just can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.89,0:49:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't want somebody on the front line
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.89,0:49:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,who just can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.89,0:49:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You think they want you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.89,0:49:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.89,0:49:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, listen, in the meantime,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.89,0:49:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all going to be hungry when we get through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.89,0:49:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How about chopping up the thing and cooking?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.89,0:49:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.89,0:49:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can contribute to,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.89,0:49:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to become a turncoat.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.89,0:49:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to become a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.89,0:49:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.89,0:49:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so a person of conscience doesn't grandstand about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.89,0:49:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Political science is 220.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.08,0:49:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's running the academia now?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.08,0:49:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to be in the mid-400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.08,0:49:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's now in 175, 185.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.08,0:49:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At its highest, it's 235.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.08,0:49:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Political science at 220.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.08,0:49:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,President of Iran,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.40,0:49:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's at 80, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.40,0:49:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't write his name out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.40,0:49:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,President of Iran,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.47,0:49:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,does your write out his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.47,0:49:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You got plenty of ink in the pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.47,0:49:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just said,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.47,0:49:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,President of Iran,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.47,0:49:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Social science at 240.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.47,0:49:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sociology, 260.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.47,0:49:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you notice the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.47,0:49:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,between the Encyclopedia Britannica and Wikipedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.47,0:50:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wikipedia calibrates at 280.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.79,0:50:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Encyclopedia Britannica is at 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.79,0:50:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When I looked up information on the history of Islam and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.79,0:50:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually really studied it quite seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.79,0:50:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I used the sources of information,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.82,0:50:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,things that were printed before the Cold War,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.82,0:50:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,before the current era.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.82,0:50:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the history of Islam before current contention about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.85,0:50:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.85,0:50:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,written in 1911 by a student of the Vatican.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.85,0:50:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Encyclopedia Britannica as I ever printed in the late 80s.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.17,0:50:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I wanted information that was unprejudiced,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.36,0:50:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,unslanted by current things.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.36,0:50:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I write up,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.36,0:50:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I write up as the history of our Islam.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.97,0:50:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book Truth Versus Falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.97,0:50:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it from sources that were,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.97,0:50:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as I was concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.97,0:50:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,uncontaminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.97,0:51:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any contention at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.97,0:51:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So these things are drummed into your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.41,0:51:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a channel that drums these memes into your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.41,0:51:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One worldism, all this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.15,0:51:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One man's terrorist is another man's freedom fighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.15,0:51:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,comes on repetitiously,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.15,0:51:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on certain TV channels.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.18,0:51:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Over and over they repeat this.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.18,0:51:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do they repeat it over and over?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.18,0:51:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it hundreds and hundreds and hundreds of times?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.92,0:51:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact in our society is that Reuters
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.75,0:51:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will not report the truth of anything anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.75,0:51:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because when you ask them about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.75,0:51:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they quote this.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.75,0:51:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Reuters dictum of truth telling, 185.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.75,0:51:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why the,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.13,0:51:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,news commentators are in despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.23,0:51:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't even trust a news release from Reuters.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.23,0:52:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 185 because they've already screened it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.23,0:52:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,through a political distortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.23,0:52:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,One man's fighter is a big difference
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.19,0:52:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,between a terrorist,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.19,0:52:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Lenin was a terrorist,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.19,0:52:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and a freedom fighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.48,0:52:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a freedom fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.12,0:52:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So that destruction of the capacity of the human mind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.30,0:52:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to differentiate truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.30,0:52:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is what I'm concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.30,0:52:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That if you're brainwashed continuously enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.59,0:52:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you will end up injured,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.62,0:52:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and your apparatus will no longer be able to filter out
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.62,0:52:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and see things that in my generation
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.62,0:52:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,were clear and obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.62,0:52:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can explain it to a young person
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.62,0:52:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and they don't even see it when you explain it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.62,0:52:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because they have been so brainwashed,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.94,0:52:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even try to talk to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.97,0:52:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because they've been so hopelessly brainwashed,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.97,0:52:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to decondition them
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.97,0:52:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so they could begin to think again on their own
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.97,0:52:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and respect what is logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.97,0:53:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the counterfeit dollar bill
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.04,0:53:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is not as good as the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.04,0:53:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll meet again after lunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.04,0:53:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.20,0:53:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okie doke.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.24,0:53:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's enough of truth for a guy's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.24,0:53:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to ruin people's lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.41,0:53:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Common belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.41,0:53:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Common belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.41,0:53:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A meme is a slogan that's repeated so often
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.41,0:54:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that it becomes uncritically accepted as truth
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.41,0:54:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and realigns your orientation towards reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.41,0:54:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's not exactly innocent or benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.12,0:54:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Conscious people shouldn't be aware
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.12,0:54:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of what they're being programmed with,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.12,0:54:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and if in doubt, you calibrate it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.12,0:54:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or if you can't calibrate it, find somebody who can,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.12,0:54:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or you email us, we'll calibrate it, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.12,0:54:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the way to God through devotion to truth
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.91,0:54:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is sort of a unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.91,0:54:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,way of expressing it, expressing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.91,0:54:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands a lot of the traditional
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.91,0:54:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,ecclesiastic trappings
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.91,0:54:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and belief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.91,0:54:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things that go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.91,0:54:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.91,0:54:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a way to God for the modern mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.91,0:54:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's designed for the modern mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.91,0:54:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,which is also scientific and reasonable,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.91,0:54:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and feels better if things could also be explained
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.07,0:54:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in a logical form.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.07,0:54:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And by seeing that spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.07,0:55:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as just a different paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.07,0:55:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's along the same scale of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.07,0:55:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is really quite a big help
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.07,0:55:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to that intellectual block.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.10,0:55:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.10,0:55:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to not lecture as long this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.10,0:55:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We need more time for questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.10,0:55:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you have questions and answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.10,0:55:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe even during the lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.10,0:55:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll answer them if we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.10,0:55:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is your own group and your own people,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.10,0:55:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're all evolving,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.10,0:55:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're all evolving together.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.10,0:55:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all in the same boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.10,0:55:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We're like a bunch of birds
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.68,0:55:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that tend to swoop onto this planet together,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.68,0:55:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're all going to be swooping off together, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.68,0:55:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that time scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.68,0:55:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,50 years one way or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.68,0:55:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't count, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.68,0:55:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A few birds get to the island first,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.68,0:55:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and some get there belatedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.68,0:55:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but generally you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.68,0:55:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're all here right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.68,0:55:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously we belong to some kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.68,0:55:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,large overall grouping, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.68,0:55:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never asked that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.68,0:56:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us here present belong to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.18,0:56:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a karmically comparable migration of birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.18,0:56:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're all a grouping, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.18,0:56:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We come on the planet together,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.18,0:56:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we evolve for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.18,0:56:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,share a lot of stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.18,0:56:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we go back on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.18,0:56:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we come back on again.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.18,0:56:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've all been together before.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.18,0:56:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that nice to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.18,0:56:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.50,0:56:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I remembered that one guy from...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.50,0:56:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,1492, I think it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.50,0:56:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've always had that intuitive knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.72,0:56:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that we come out and we somehow swoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.72,0:56:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Like tends to go to like, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.72,0:56:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're all like in our essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.72,0:56:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, some are bigger birds than other birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.72,0:56:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Some have better feathers and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.49,0:56:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Which of course is not fair, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.49,0:56:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's got to be called shorty.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.20,0:56:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.54,0:57:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So I volunteered.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.54,0:57:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I volunteered.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.54,0:57:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, we need a few more shorties
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.54,0:57:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,before we go back to the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.54,0:57:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay, I'll be a shorty.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.57,0:57:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.57,0:57:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're all here of our own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.57,0:57:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make sure of that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.57,0:57:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.57,0:57:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all here of our own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.64,0:57:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we're all here of our own free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.64,0:57:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,having chosen to incarnate,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.64,0:57:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,having had an option,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.64,0:57:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and having chosen what we thought was
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.64,0:57:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the greatest spiritual merit or benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.64,0:57:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, we're a pretty committed group,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.64,0:57:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,even on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.83,0:57:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.89,0:57:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're a pretty committed group,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.89,0:57:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,even on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.89,0:57:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.89,0:57:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They're happy to hang out, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.99,0:57:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very comfortable heavenly space.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.99,0:57:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, there's a lot of areas of heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.99,0:57:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And we don't hang out in lazy heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.99,0:57:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all them lazy ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.99,0:57:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,just hang out there, listen to music,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.99,0:58:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,listen to the angels sing, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.99,0:58:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,having a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.72,0:58:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's us worker bees, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.52,0:58:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind is currently 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.52,0:58:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was up to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.96,0:58:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's at 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.96,0:58:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know who's responsible, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.96,0:58:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe if we hate them enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.96,0:58:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll go back up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.92,0:58:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, somebody out there is dragging their feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.08,0:58:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll have to speak to them
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.14,0:58:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when we find out who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.68,0:58:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Except they can't spell their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.68,0:58:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.45,0:58:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were we on these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.45,0:59:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,93.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.16,0:59:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, 93.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.70,0:59:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.05,0:59:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.05,0:59:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, is there anything we brought up?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.01,0:59:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I want 93.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.01,0:59:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.01,0:59:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything we brought up
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.01,0:59:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have a question about?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.25,0:59:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.25,0:59:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There, that's a good slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.28,0:59:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the last one?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.28,0:59:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.28,0:59:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's memes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.28,0:59:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to make sure we were done with memes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.28,0:59:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's hard to be aware
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.43,0:59:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're being programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.43,0:59:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're being programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.56,0:59:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we did perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.26,0:59:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's what triggered this slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.26,0:59:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When he came out and said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.26,0:59:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is part of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.26,0:59:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,perception is reality, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.26,0:59:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,yo, yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.26,0:59:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.26,0:59:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we have lack of intellectual integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.29,0:59:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.29,0:59:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.29,0:59:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.29,1:00:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's undermining academia is not perception,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.29,1:00:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but philosophic theories, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.29,1:00:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the last one before the last?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.55,1:00:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.55,1:00:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.55,1:00:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.61,1:00:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.03,1:00:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to see,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.03,1:00:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the world we're looking at?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.03,1:00:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to reach a more advanced level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.38,1:00:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to be aware of what the traps are.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.38,1:00:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is one of the current traps.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.38,1:00:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason this is a trap is because it's not just devoted
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.38,1:00:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to somebody sitting in the back of the library
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.38,1:00:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,looking up some French relativistic philosopher
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.38,1:00:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to report on in class.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.38,1:00:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is part of the media barrage.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.38,1:00:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the media barrage that hits you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.38,1:00:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of times a day, unknowingly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.41,1:00:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in other words,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.73,1:00:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the idea of being brainwashed without your permission,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.73,1:00:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,without your permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.73,1:00:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like, you know, if you said to me,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.76,1:00:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,would you like to be brainwashed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.76,1:01:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with something that calibrates the lesson of truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.76,1:01:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people would say no,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.76,1:01:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but they eagerly flip the switch on the TV
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.76,1:01:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,from one brainwash to another.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.76,1:01:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the purpose is merely to be aware
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.34,1:01:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is a phenomenon,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.34,1:01:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that other generations didn't have to grow up in.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.34,1:01:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the Ku Klux Klan was pretty overt.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.34,1:01:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't being subtly reprogrammed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.34,1:01:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very out there, very, very blatant.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.34,1:01:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And Nazism, all the things that were fallacious
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.34,1:01:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in that generation, wasn't surreptitious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.34,1:01:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The propaganda courts,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.34,1:01:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the propaganda minister of the Nazi regime
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.34,1:01:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was an expert.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.34,1:01:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.34,1:01:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And his directions are being followed today.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.34,1:01:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the far left actually followed his directions,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.34,1:01:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you repeat a lie often enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.34,1:01:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind will begin to believe that it's truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.34,1:01:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to become aware when you're being programmed,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.34,1:02:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when you hear some kind of a theme
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.34,1:02:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,repeated over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.37,1:02:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I watch the History Channel
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.37,1:02:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the International History Channel,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.37,1:02:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and you hear some of these things repeated so often,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.37,1:02:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,just be aware.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.01,1:02:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you get more advanced in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.01,1:02:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and get the essence rather than the perception,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.01,1:02:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to intuit when you're getting brainwashed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.01,1:02:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what's wrong with it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.01,1:02:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's something wrong with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.01,1:02:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds good, but there's something wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.01,1:02:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with the way it's presented
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.01,1:02:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or the way it's being utilized.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.01,1:02:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, sometimes you can utilize
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.01,1:02:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what is taken out of context as truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.17,1:02:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but placed in the context in which it's presented
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.17,1:02:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is no longer as truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.17,1:02:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They're using truth to support fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.17,1:02:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the subtlety of how to use truth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.17,1:02:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to support fallacy, and this is one.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.17,1:02:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say, yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.17,1:02:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This all depends on the point of view,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.17,1:03:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's only part of the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.17,1:03:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,By leaving out the other part of the story,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.17,1:03:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up just being reprogrammed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.17,1:03:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The moral high ground, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.27,1:03:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is you're looking at what Palestine
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.27,1:03:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and Israel, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.27,1:03:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at the whole Middle East.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.27,1:03:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's got the moral high ground?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.27,1:03:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And moral high ground is sought
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.27,1:03:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is then deemed to be justification.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.27,1:03:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can get the moral high ground
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.27,1:03:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and rationalize something,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.27,1:03:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have permission to do whatever you wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.74,1:03:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I think that's all we wanted to really say about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.74,1:03:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any questions you have about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.74,1:03:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You want anything clarified here?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.77,1:03:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that's unclear?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.70,1:03:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to make it as clear as possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.70,1:03:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing I like about consciousness calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.70,1:03:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is everybody can understand the number, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.70,1:03:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I said, if you made the numbers like money,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.70,1:03:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,would you pay $80 to have this guy come and, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.70,1:04:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,would you pay him this kind of money for an $80 lecture?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.70,1:04:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He gets $5,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.80,1:04:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you went to the University of Wisconsin
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.80,1:04:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,paying your taxpayer money $5,000
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.80,1:04:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to this paranoid, delusional guy who calibrates at 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.80,1:04:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if you put it in dollars and cents,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.59,1:04:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,well, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.59,1:04:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if it costs you money, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.59,1:04:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If it costs you money, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.59,1:04:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's see the next one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.78,1:04:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.08,1:04:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Next number, Maury.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.67,1:04:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the photo, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.03,1:04:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what number that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.67,1:04:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, this was the celebration of the Tuskegee Squadron.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.72,1:04:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was celebrated worldwide there,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.36,1:04:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,not worldwide, in the country,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.36,1:04:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,various places in the country a few weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.36,1:04:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This was sent by Nancy from St. Petersburg, Florida,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.36,1:04:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from the local paper.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.36,1:05:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a big thing on the front paper.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.36,1:05:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got it through the expertise of Robert and our staff,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.36,1:05:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could show it on a slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.36,1:05:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When I looked at it, I said, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.49,1:05:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And a friend that was close to us looked at it and he says,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.62,1:05:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the first time I saw that, he says, what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.97,1:05:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It ran up and down my spine.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.97,1:05:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call those pimples?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.97,1:05:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Chills.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.97,1:05:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Chills, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.19,1:05:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Chills, chills and goose pimples.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.19,1:05:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Goosebumps, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.19,1:05:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Chills and goose bumps was an instant reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.19,1:05:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw it, I was stunned by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.19,1:05:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something mystical, incredible about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.19,1:05:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is one of the original members.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.19,1:05:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.25,1:05:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They had their 50th anniversary, I think,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.25,1:05:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and most of them are dead now.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.25,1:05:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, you remember when I went on the service,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.38,1:05:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it was still racial prejudice,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.38,1:05:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the service just assumed that black people
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.38,1:06:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,would take jobs such as the kitchen steward or physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.89,1:06:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the way the military was.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.89,1:06:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't particularly like it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.99,1:06:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because I grew up in an environment where no such thinking occurred,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.99,1:06:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seemed to be the military tradition,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.99,1:06:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so I figured, well, whatever it is, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.99,1:06:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And we lived with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.99,1:06:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Tuskegee Squadron, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.99,1:06:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,was the most perfect squadron in the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.05,1:06:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They never lost a single bomber.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.31,1:06:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.31,1:06:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.31,1:06:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All black.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.37,1:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Never lost a single bomber.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.37,1:06:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A perfect score.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.76,1:06:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I was a bomber pilot, that's the squadron.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.56,1:06:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I'm protecting your butt.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.56,1:06:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A score of 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.72,1:06:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.91,1:06:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, and the Tuskegee Squadron calibrated at 480,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.48,1:06:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is excellence.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.48,1:06:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,480 is excellence.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.52,1:07:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is one of the survivors.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.52,1:07:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I looked at his face.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.52,1:07:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I can't believe this face.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.68,1:07:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's almost an angelic, mystical aura that comes out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.68,1:07:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you feel it,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.68,1:07:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's more than just a person.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.68,1:07:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't look at it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.68,1:07:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you want to cry,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.68,1:07:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's something very mystical about it, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.68,1:07:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you see it or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.68,1:07:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an entrancing quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.68,1:07:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like an...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.68,1:07:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,an incarnated angelic being or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.74,1:07:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something behind this face.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.74,1:07:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I thought at 480,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.74,1:07:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that sort of puts the nail in prejudice against black people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.80,1:07:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, you know, as far as the military went,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.80,1:07:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the end of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.80,1:07:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect score at 480.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.00,1:07:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there's something mystical about that gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.05,1:07:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.05,1:08:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.05,1:08:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was sent to us by Nancy
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.05,1:08:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from St. Petersburg, Florida,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.05,1:08:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,from the front page of the St. Petersburg newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.31,1:08:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a few weeks ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.31,1:08:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they met here in Phoenix, too,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.31,1:08:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the final...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.31,1:08:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So not many members of the original Tuskegee squadron are alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.31,1:08:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the prejudice, then, against black...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.14,1:08:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,other than Caucasians
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.14,1:08:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is not eliminated by counter-propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.14,1:08:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's overcome by reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.14,1:08:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy here is reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.14,1:08:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,480, perfect score.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.14,1:08:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What more do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.14,1:08:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reality of their essence is what wins in the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.14,1:08:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You automatically rise to the level of your own inner reality
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.14,1:08:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,without having to propagandize it by favoritism.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.14,1:08:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think favoritism towards women and minorities
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.14,1:08:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is insulting and diminishes their achievements.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.14,1:09:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it diminishes their stature.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.14,1:09:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's insulting.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.14,1:09:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, I've never gone for preferential treatment of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.14,1:09:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People are equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.14,1:09:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They should be treated as equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.14,1:09:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so here you see an equal at 480.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.14,1:09:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very excellent.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.14,1:09:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's higher than the great books of the Western world, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.14,1:09:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's truth plus excellence.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.14,1:09:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really super excellent.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.14,1:09:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So that shows a transition in our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.14,1:09:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not due to...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.14,1:09:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get there because there was anti-black parades, pro-black parades.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.14,1:09:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't get here with parades or spiritual protest.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.14,1:09:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You got here out of the fact that essence stands...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.14,1:09:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of truth stands for itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.33,1:09:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something stunning about this person.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.33,1:09:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we still don't know what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.33,1:09:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps some people will have some visions or dreams or intuitions about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.33,1:09:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I may not know what to ask that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.33,1:09:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of entrancing, wouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.33,1:09:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.49,1:10:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.49,1:10:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll turn him off because I can't really think and talk when he's up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.49,1:10:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Some kind of an angelic being is all I can...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.49,1:10:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of my mind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.49,1:10:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We may have all known for really great periods of time, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.49,1:10:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.26,1:10:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I thought we would have more...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.26,1:10:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to close the lecture early and have more time for questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.96,1:10:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought before we do it, sort of like we do on the Wednesday night,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.96,1:10:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,informal sessions, we might just have any spontaneous questions that arise.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.96,1:10:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once we start with the questions and answers, those are individual.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.96,1:10:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody need a clarification, something that's not clear?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.96,1:10:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.96,1:10:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate at the high consciousness that you are, why do you need muscle testing?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.12,1:10:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Who said you need it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.76,1:10:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I see you do it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.76,1:10:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's for teaching purposes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.76,1:11:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the essence of a thing the minute I have the question in my head.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.92,1:11:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.92,1:11:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't help other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.92,1:11:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for teaching purposes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.92,1:11:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you can bring it from the...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.92,1:11:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can bring it into the physical domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.30,1:11:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To many people, it's the physical demonstration that convinces people.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.30,1:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To intuit it and know it, there's many ways of knowing it and verifying it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.30,1:11:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And also the muscle response is not the only one.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.30,1:11:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're working on research with the pupillary response and other physiologic responses.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.30,1:11:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought it's interesting that protoplasm knew this from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.36,1:11:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the knowledge is buried within protoplasm itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.36,1:11:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And can be revealed again through its exposure through protoplasmic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.36,1:11:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as consciousness goes, a person with more advanced consciousness doesn't need that to tell essence from perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.36,1:12:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus spots the fakes from the real early in the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.43,1:12:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The real problem then is the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.38,1:12:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is convinced it knows, whereas actually it doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.67,1:12:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What it thinks...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.67,1:12:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What it confuses are beliefs as truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.67,1:12:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people believe it, therefore it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.67,1:12:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thought the earth was flat.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.67,1:12:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't make it true, did it?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.67,1:12:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.67,1:12:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Prevailing opinion then is not a very good direction of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.67,1:12:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because 100% of people can be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.67,1:12:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Also we see the consciousness level of mankind in general has gone down two points.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.67,1:12:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's a logarithmic number, that's significant.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.67,1:12:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To go from 207 to 205 means that things are not as integrous as they were just a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.67,1:12:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in class we calibrated the level of consciousness of mankind many times.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.70,1:13:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw it go up to 207 and now we see it's declined to 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.70,1:13:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A combination of the factors we've been talking about in the last few slides.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.70,1:13:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the corruption of the definition and capacity to recognize truth is the main thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.70,1:13:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.83,1:13:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's due to the disruption of the capacity to recognize truth that causes the drop, resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.40,1:13:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.40,1:13:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the arm is really a demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.40,1:13:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.40,1:13:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A confirmation from another non-intellectual domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.40,1:13:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Her arm doesn't think.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.40,1:13:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And she doesn't think.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.40,1:13:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I just asked the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.40,1:13:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't think about the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.40,1:13:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the time I don't even tell her what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.40,1:13:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The way we do it at home, because she's busy doing something.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.40,1:13:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll say, what I'm holding in mind calibrates over 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.40,1:13:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,570.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.40,1:13:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,575.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.60,1:13:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,580.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.60,1:13:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,590.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.60,1:14:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was holding, what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.36,1:14:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Stigmata.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.36,1:14:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Stigmata.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.42,1:14:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was holding stigmata in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.61,1:14:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the stigmata real or are they fantasy?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.61,1:14:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it hysterical phenomena?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.61,1:14:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody looks for some medical explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.61,1:14:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Some reductionistic, materialistic, rational sounding reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.12,1:14:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the intensity of devotion, it's a spontaneous phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.12,1:14:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Father Pugh and many of the number of mystics throughout history have had it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.12,1:14:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.12,1:14:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.12,1:14:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.12,1:14:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The devotion is so intense with the divine figure that one becomes, begins to manifest
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.12,1:14:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the phenomena attributed to the divine figure, you see, intense divine devotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.12,1:14:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, she doesn't have to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.12,1:14:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When I said she doesn't have to think, she doesn't know what I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.12,1:14:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying what I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.12,1:14:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My suspicion was that it's about 570 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.12,1:15:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's around 570 that the so-called city's paranormal, extra-normal, super-normal
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.12,1:15:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena begin to appear.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.12,1:15:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all occur spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.12,1:15:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I had them going for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.12,1:15:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will tell you, they are spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.12,1:15:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's more surprised than yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.12,1:15:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena occur of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.12,1:15:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Not caused by anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.54,1:15:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.54,1:15:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality exists within the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.54,1:15:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the field, the action, the potentiality becomes an actuality through the power of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.73,1:15:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.73,1:15:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All things manifest by virtue of potential becoming actual when the energy is appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.76,1:15:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, as the Heisenberg principle shows us, intention is powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.76,1:15:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention already influences whether a potential is going to become an actual and manifest
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.17,1:15:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as an emergence within the three dilemmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.17,1:15:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.17,1:16:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.34,1:16:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.43,1:16:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.43,1:16:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, probably, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.43,1:16:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get started here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.81,1:16:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Any other questions? Yes? Go ahead, lady. Woman?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.63,1:16:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you elaborate and talk about the 11 days that you surrendered at the thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.93,1:16:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to have to ask him to repeat the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.57,1:16:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you elaborate on the 11 days that you surrendered at the thoughts as they arose,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.77,1:16:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on how those days went?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.92,1:16:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you hear what she's saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.70,1:16:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The 11 days that you surrendered at the thoughts as they arose, how that happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.02,1:16:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody know what she said?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.04,1:17:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In your personal experience, you talked about you went through a period of 11 days
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.18,1:17:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,where you surrendered all your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.06,1:17:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.40,1:17:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you elaborate on that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.00,1:17:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.90,1:17:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's what I call the final run.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.06,1:17:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I put it in previous books.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.96,1:17:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm touching it in this book.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.48,1:17:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a final run.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.94,1:17:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You develop a certain amount of spiritual momentum.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.74,1:17:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You start doing a spiritual practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.20,1:17:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes habitual.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.16,1:17:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you begin to move forward in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.52,1:17:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're seeing things from a more expanded level.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.70,1:17:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you see things to apply it to that you didn't see before.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.70,1:17:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjectively, you're aware that you can feel the energy coming up.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.10,1:17:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The commitment to reach the ultimate truth becomes overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.53,1:17:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything in your life becomes second to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.40,1:17:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't interrupt the meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.28,1:18:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I did an hour in the morning, hour at night for some 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.20,1:18:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I quit the world and would meditate really constantly for months on end.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.62,1:18:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditative state.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.44,1:18:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There comes what I call the final run where you turn off the television.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.72,1:18:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't read anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.16,1:18:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.34,1:18:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You might visit some spiritual groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.14,1:18:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But your spiritual practice is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.84,1:18:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.92,1:18:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Every thought is turned over as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.66,1:18:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're trying to do in our own language here in the lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.28,1:18:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is realize that which is prior to the processor.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.46,1:18:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading edge of the ego is that little amoeba out there
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.82,1:18:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that is sensing and processing everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.49,1:18:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality of the information gathered is one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.26,1:18:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear the music one ten-thousandth of a second later.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.04,1:18:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You play it off the playback.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.98,1:19:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the earphones you have on is hearing the music
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.50,1:19:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that just happened one ten-thousandth of a second before.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.64,1:19:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not getting a direct reading from reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.08,1:19:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting the relay, the modulation of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.47,1:19:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As the thinkingness falls away and the silence prevails,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.15,1:19:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,those things that are surrendered to God become more and more profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.03,1:19:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.87,1:19:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They come as a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.47,1:19:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They come as a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.05,1:19:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the willingness to surrender that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.89,1:19:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And that opens for a greater revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.55,1:19:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the experiencing of the essence begins to expand.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.35,1:19:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes greater and greater and greater.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.79,1:19:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, you come to existence itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.52,1:19:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the willingness to surrender the desire for existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.60,1:19:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,After existence, at least in this would happen in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.38,1:20:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was everything that is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.22,1:20:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no interdependencies.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.18,1:20:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no entities there.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.02,1:20:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,People talk to entities on the other side of the long left.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.26,1:20:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no entities there.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.08,1:20:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no one there because it's completely nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.38,1:20:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's almost like the essence of existence itself has been transcended.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.94,1:20:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're beyond either existence versus nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.30,1:20:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the one I got at age three.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.28,1:20:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence versus nonexistence was the conundrum of this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.02,1:20:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you really experience it now
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.46,1:20:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at a higher level.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.56,1:20:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember, I think I've told you that the knowingness came in.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.33,1:20:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you are beyond all accountability, all power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.55,1:20:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Claim it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.77,1:20:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Own it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.79,1:20:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.01,1:20:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not answerable to anything or anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.26,1:20:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've let go of emotional love.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.80,1:20:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's therefore, all power is yours came as a knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.84,1:21:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that state of knowingness was the silent awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.46,1:21:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That all power is already mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.19,1:21:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would I want with it?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.19,1:21:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the reality of realization.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.19,1:21:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I was, was infinitely power, omnipotent, omniscient.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.19,1:21:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.19,1:21:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And what would be the gain?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.19,1:21:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the Luciferic temptation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.19,1:21:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's where Lucifer fell, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.19,1:21:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to own the power out of pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.19,1:21:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just the power, but the pride of the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.19,1:21:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at that way, then I denied it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.19,1:21:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what the only thing left, the only thing left,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.19,1:21:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was the power of the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.48,1:21:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the only thing left.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.02,1:21:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing left.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.02,1:21:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All the content of consciousness had been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.02,1:21:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dissolved, surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.02,1:21:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There was only life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.02,1:21:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the last thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.02,1:21:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The self as the source of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.40,1:21:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And this too, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.40,1:21:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized this too, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.40,1:21:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This too, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.40,1:21:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I must surrender to Thee.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.40,1:21:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I surrendered life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.88,1:22:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then was agony.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.88,1:22:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Agony, I will not kid you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.88,1:22:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ferocious agony.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.20,1:22:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And the experience of dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.20,1:22:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go through the death agony.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.16,1:22:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the other side, ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.16,1:22:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The glory of God shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.39,1:22:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the radiance of all existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.39,1:22:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that all of creation is divine.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.39,1:22:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the radiance of divinity shining forth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.39,1:22:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,out of everything that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.39,1:22:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get used to it after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.55,1:22:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get used to it after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.55,1:22:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get used to it after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.55,1:22:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get used to it after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.55,1:22:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get used to it after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.55,1:22:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get used to it after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.55,1:22:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the beginning, everything you look at
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.55,1:22:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,almost knocks you over with its beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.55,1:22:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the essence of divinity shining forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.55,1:22:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the essence of divinity shining forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.87,1:22:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.87,1:22:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloria in excelsis Deo.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.87,1:22:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning, all that is, is God.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.28,1:22:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning, all that is, is God.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.38,1:22:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And somehow that same essence shines through
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.38,1:22:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And somehow that same essence shines through
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.38,1:22:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that photograph.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.38,1:22:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I start to go back in the state
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.38,1:23:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when I look at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.38,1:23:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm talking so that keeps me out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.38,1:23:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When I stop talking and
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.38,1:23:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,look at it for half a minute or something
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.38,1:23:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,look at it for half a minute or something
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.38,1:23:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll quit talking and you're all frankly
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.38,1:23:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on your own then.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.38,1:23:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason I repeat this
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.55,1:23:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because the question will arise
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.55,1:23:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is two bumps.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.55,1:23:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One at 850, which is the void.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.55,1:23:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've tried to give people guidance on how to get across that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.55,1:23:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's nothing written about it hardly at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.55,1:23:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's practically nothing written about
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.55,1:23:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the final doorway.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.55,1:23:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So I write about the two things to which to me
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.55,1:23:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual literature
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.55,1:23:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the entities who went through them
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.55,1:23:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,took the information with them and left.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.55,1:23:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But somehow in the aura
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.55,1:23:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But somehow in the aura
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.55,1:23:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it was in this aura
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.55,1:23:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because it came forth as a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.55,1:23:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it was not a thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.55,1:23:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow in this aura
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.55,1:23:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,was already the knowingness of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.55,1:24:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.55,1:24:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness was already within the aura.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.55,1:24:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness was in the aura.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.55,1:24:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't find the answer in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.55,1:24:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can search your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.55,1:24:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to find that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.16,1:24:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But the knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.16,1:24:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that all fear is fallacious
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.83,1:24:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a maxim in Zen meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.83,1:24:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I belong to the first Zen institute in America
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.83,1:24:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the 50s.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.83,1:24:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.83,1:24:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, based on the confidence
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.83,1:24:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that must have come in at a very high vibration
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.83,1:24:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because I surrendered my life to that truth
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.83,1:24:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and walked through that door
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.83,1:24:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you it was agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.83,1:24:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But the agony is brief.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.83,1:24:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And then on the other side
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.83,1:24:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the door
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.83,1:24:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is ecstasy beyond definition.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.50,1:24:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.50,1:24:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is an expression of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.50,1:24:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In that state
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.50,1:24:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.50,1:24:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.50,1:24:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see it shining forth
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.50,1:24:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone who exists
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.50,1:25:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,just like I thought this picture
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.50,1:25:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason I picked it out
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.50,1:25:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is because I think it's easy to see
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.27,1:25:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the radiance of divinity shining forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.27,1:25:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost a mystical state
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.27,1:25:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,when you look at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.27,1:25:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was a gift to me
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.27,1:25:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was glad to share it with everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.27,1:25:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to thank Nancy from St. Augustine
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.27,1:25:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for sending it to the group.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.27,1:25:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead, you were going to ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.04,1:25:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there's the physical brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.12,1:25:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit exists as
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.12,1:25:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,non-material.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.12,1:25:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.22,1:25:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an energy field independent
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.22,1:25:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of the physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.22,1:25:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's a karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.22,1:25:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment of birth, everyone already has a
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.22,1:25:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.22,1:25:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So where did you get it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.22,1:25:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the spirit, which is non-physical
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.22,1:26:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,maintains
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.22,1:26:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.32,1:26:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we're all here together
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.32,1:26:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is because we have a common
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.32,1:26:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a flock energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.32,1:26:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We all
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.32,1:26:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are red pigeons, or whatever we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.32,1:26:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We sense their energy
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.32,1:26:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're attracted to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.41,1:26:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.60,1:26:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,people say, well, Christians don't believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.60,1:26:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They do. Of course they believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.60,1:26:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't call it karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.60,1:26:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think original sin is?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.76,1:26:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you need a savior for?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.76,1:26:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're born with a negative karma of man's sinfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.76,1:26:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and fall from grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.76,1:26:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear of Adam and Eve?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.76,1:26:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever hear of the apple? Did you ever hear of the viper?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.76,1:26:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, sure you got karma. What the hell do you need a savior for?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.76,1:26:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.40,1:26:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You got plenty of karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.40,1:26:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And after you leave this body, you got heaven, hell, or purgatory.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.40,1:26:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Christians tell me they don't believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.40,1:26:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you don't believe in that term
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.40,1:26:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because it comes out of a different culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.40,1:26:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But you certainly believe in spiritual responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.40,1:26:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and destiny
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.40,1:26:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and a reality that goes beyond this
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.40,1:27:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,particular lifetime, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.79,1:27:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forgot what the question was.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.79,1:27:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.58,1:27:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so independent of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.58,1:27:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,once the kundalini, at level 200
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.58,1:27:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.58,1:27:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to flow up the chakra system.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.58,1:27:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It energizes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.58,1:27:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a shift in brain physiology
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.58,1:27:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to the right brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.58,1:27:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Information is processed
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.58,1:27:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,differently. It bypasses the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.58,1:27:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,amygdala.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.58,1:27:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of responding emotionally
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.58,1:27:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with cannons, fight or flight,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.58,1:27:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you release endorphins because
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.58,1:27:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to see and experience life as
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.58,1:27:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,benign and loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.58,1:27:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is benign and loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.68,1:27:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the animal kingdom, it starts out
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.68,1:27:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with the mother. So the motherhood
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.68,1:27:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is, to me, the source of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.68,1:27:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential love.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.68,1:27:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The first appearance is through the maternal.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.68,1:27:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The etheric brain then
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.90,1:27:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,exists independently
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.90,1:27:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.90,1:27:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When you go out of the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.90,1:27:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you're very much who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.90,1:28:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're very much aware.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.90,1:28:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see and hear, experience and think.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.90,1:28:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a sense of identity.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.90,1:28:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's totally non-physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.90,1:28:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can look down at the physical body
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.90,1:28:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the most boring thing in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.90,1:28:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You would think, gee, I'd sure miss my physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.90,1:28:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't. In fact, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.90,1:28:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in it, you're reluctant.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.06,1:28:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing attractive about it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.06,1:28:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you're complete and total just the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.06,1:28:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.06,1:28:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,through all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.06,1:28:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I like being there because
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.06,1:28:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to take the train. I can just think there
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.06,1:28:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm there.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.38,1:28:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I want to go to Alaska, I just think Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.38,1:28:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Bang. I'm in Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.38,1:28:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm in a non...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.38,1:28:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to travel.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.38,1:28:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So having a body is a drag.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.38,1:28:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to haul it everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.38,1:28:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to meet somebody, you think them.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.38,1:28:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.38,1:28:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the etheric realm is very nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.38,1:28:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.41,1:28:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it's weightless.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.41,1:28:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It moves the minute you think.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.41,1:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think the other side of the room,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.44,1:28:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you are on the other side of the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.44,1:29:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no time delay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.44,1:29:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, you have all your faculties.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.44,1:29:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the sense of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.44,1:29:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of self goes with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.44,1:29:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the etheric body
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.44,1:29:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,can be seen by their clairvoyance,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.44,1:29:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, people who see them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.44,1:29:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The etheric bodies
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.44,1:29:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are spiritual in nature
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.44,1:29:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've been named over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.44,1:29:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Esoterically named.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.44,1:29:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one above the crown chakra
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.44,1:29:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.44,1:29:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then beyond that is the buddhic body
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.44,1:29:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.57,1:29:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,etnic body
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.57,1:29:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and I forget the names of all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.57,1:29:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to know all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.57,1:29:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Esotericism.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.57,1:29:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, the chakra system goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.57,1:29:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,above the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.57,1:29:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a chakra here, another chakra here,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.57,1:29:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,another chakra here.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.57,1:29:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the crown chakra is at the top,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.57,1:29:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.57,1:29:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Opening the third eye of the buddhic body
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.57,1:29:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,means that you get essence
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.57,1:29:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.57,1:29:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I like that photograph I showed
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.57,1:29:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is you get the essence of that being
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.57,1:30:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which is way beyond his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.57,1:30:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the appearance sociologically
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.57,1:30:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd say, well, he's a black guy to begin with
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.57,1:30:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's a military guy to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.57,1:30:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Start labeling him and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.57,1:30:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You instantly get the essence,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.57,1:30:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the purity, the innocence, the radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.57,1:30:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the divinity shining forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.57,1:30:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.70,1:30:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the etheric bodies then
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.70,1:30:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have the same chakra systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.70,1:30:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.70,1:30:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is far more complicated
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.70,1:30:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because you also have the archetypes
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.70,1:30:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you've inherited within the human domain
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.70,1:30:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the archetypes by Carl Jung.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.70,1:30:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of the archetypes
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.70,1:30:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is an energy field within you
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.70,1:30:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and each of those archetypes also has a chakra system.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.70,1:30:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as I've mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.70,1:30:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the only problem I really had with spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.70,1:30:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.70,1:30:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.70,1:30:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of the spiritual knight
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.70,1:30:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,getting indignant over fallacy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.70,1:30:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and killing innocent children.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.70,1:30:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The knight would come up again
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.70,1:30:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the crusades
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.70,1:30:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,blowing up of innocent children
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.70,1:31:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,would set me off with indignation.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.70,1:31:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I had to overcome that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.70,1:31:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and discover what it was
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.70,1:31:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrender that to God
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.70,1:31:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrender that to God
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.70,1:31:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that morality is not up to me
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.70,1:31:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrender morality to divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.70,1:31:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.34,1:31:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Lucifer fall
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.34,1:31:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when Lucifer fell?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.34,1:31:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he also
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.34,1:31:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at that point in time
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.34,1:31:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if Lucifer was an archangel
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.34,1:31:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,did he have a reduction
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.47,1:31:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in his outstanding
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.47,1:31:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,power level which archangels
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.47,1:31:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,rank at that 50%?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.47,1:31:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I'm not an expert
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.47,1:31:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,on those dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.47,1:31:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of pride, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.47,1:31:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It was pride
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.47,1:31:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power of
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.47,1:31:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,overcoming truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.47,1:31:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.47,1:31:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic sells out
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.47,1:31:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,truth for power.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.53,1:31:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The Satanic sells out love.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.53,1:31:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So Satan is
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.53,1:31:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,war, horror, torture
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.53,1:32:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all that kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.53,1:32:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Luciferic is more
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.79,1:32:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,preying upon the innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.79,1:32:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of the college students
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.79,1:32:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,with that which is fallacious
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.79,1:32:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and having them think that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.79,1:32:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a higher truth
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.79,1:32:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,than truths that calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.79,1:32:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,way much higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.79,1:32:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And trying to acquire
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.79,1:32:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.79,1:32:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's done out of pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.79,1:32:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Because humility would tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.79,1:32:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that the source of truth would be God
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.79,1:32:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wouldn't be bothered
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.79,1:32:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,challenging God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.79,1:32:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose I would want
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.79,1:32:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to challenge God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.79,1:32:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.79,1:32:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Give you a black eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.90,1:32:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been a lot of prayer for peace
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.51,1:32:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have a
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.51,1:32:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,problem with that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.51,1:32:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because of what I've learned here.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.51,1:32:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So my question is
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.51,1:32:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is there ever
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.21,1:33:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a higher evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.21,1:33:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we are not
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.21,1:33:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.21,1:33:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're asking actually the hypothetical
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.21,1:33:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's sort of aligned with what is the purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.21,1:33:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of worldly life.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.21,1:33:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And do I think that if all of us on the planet got together
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.21,1:33:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and prayed for peace we would bring about peace?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.21,1:33:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.21,1:33:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that would defeat really divine intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.21,1:33:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If this was meant to be
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.21,1:33:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a heavenly realm
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.80,1:33:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.93,1:33:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The realms that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.93,1:33:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate 600 and over
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.93,1:33:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,are the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.93,1:33:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavens are 570 and over.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.93,1:33:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,540 and over, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.93,1:33:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The celestial realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.09,1:33:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the celestial realms
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.09,1:33:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate at that level
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.09,1:33:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when you go out of body
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.09,1:33:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you are attracted to that particular realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.09,1:33:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, there are various levels
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.09,1:33:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.09,1:33:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The various energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.09,1:33:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the etheric bodies of entities
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.09,1:33:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as they leave are attracted to the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.09,1:33:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.09,1:34:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.09,1:34:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what Lucifer's problem was
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.54,1:34:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.54,1:34:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's just supposed to be prideful.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.54,1:34:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The classic falls are
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.54,1:34:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Satanic and Luciferic.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.54,1:34:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And they represent different energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.54,1:34:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.54,1:34:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,90 or below you could say
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.54,1:34:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is Satanic to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.54,1:34:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Serial killers who kill
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.54,1:34:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,50 people and dismember their bodies
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.54,1:34:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and eat them and God knows all
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.54,1:34:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of thinkable are obviously coming
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.54,1:34:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,from other dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.54,1:34:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Other dimensions who I don't want
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.54,1:34:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.54,1:34:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.80,1:34:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.23,1:34:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.35,1:34:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're speaking in a soft way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.35,1:34:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Break time.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.35,1:34:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Break who?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.35,1:34:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Break up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.56,1:34:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One more and then we'll go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.56,1:34:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You just mentioned the 12 steps.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.56,1:34:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How the 12 step program is the real
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.56,1:35:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual authentic integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.56,1:35:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.56,1:35:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I noticed
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.56,1:35:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that one of the steps is
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.56,1:35:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,made a conscious decision
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.56,1:35:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn our free will over
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.56,1:35:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to God as we understood him.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.56,1:35:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Our will. Didn't say free.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.56,1:35:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I know that one of the real
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.56,1:35:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,things of our western civilization
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.56,1:35:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is oh I have free will
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.56,1:35:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to you know create my life to be
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.56,1:35:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,free.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.56,1:35:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They mean his free ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.56,1:35:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Free ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.56,1:35:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So much myself could
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.56,1:35:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to relinquish his
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.56,1:35:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,free will and turn it over to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.56,1:35:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not free will.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.56,1:35:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's will.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.56,1:35:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We chose to surrender our will to God
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.56,1:35:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,asking only for his will for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.04,1:35:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.04,1:35:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're doing is
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.04,1:35:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendering intellectual arrogance.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.07,1:35:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.23,1:35:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,chose to surrender our will
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.55,1:35:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to God asking for his
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.55,1:35:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,guidance. Asking only for
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.55,1:36:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,his will for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.55,1:36:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.55,1:36:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,changing your
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.55,1:36:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,role. You're saying
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.55,1:36:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of my life is to be
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.55,1:36:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a servant of God
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.55,1:36:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the master of my fellow
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.55,1:36:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,men. You are trying to control
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.73,1:36:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,others. He has no opinion
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.73,1:36:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on outside issues.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.73,1:36:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't want to convert anybody to anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.73,1:36:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Any more than I want to convert.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.73,1:36:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to convert anybody to anything here do we?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.73,1:36:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who needs converting better wait
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.73,1:36:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.73,1:36:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to convert
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.73,1:36:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.73,1:36:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to convert anybody to anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.73,1:36:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,One last and then we're going to
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.73,1:36:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,break for the realignment.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.73,1:36:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is ascension an option
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.73,1:36:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of us
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.73,1:36:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,all of our
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.83,1:36:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,individualized
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.83,1:36:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,selves
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.12,1:36:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as opposed to death?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.96,1:36:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascension being?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.96,1:36:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is ascension being an option? It's a karmic option
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.96,1:37:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,having earned it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.96,1:37:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascension.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.96,1:37:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.49,1:37:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascension.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.61,1:37:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascended being?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.61,1:37:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the question is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.87,1:37:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody know what the question is?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.44,1:37:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascending.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.44,1:37:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascending.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.16,1:37:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascending. Everybody's ascending here
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.16,1:37:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or you wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.00,1:37:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want any descenders here.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.00,1:37:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All descenders leave the room
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.73,1:37:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.73,1:37:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All you ascenders
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.21,1:37:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,reassemble. We'll do questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.21,1:37:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and God bless you for all.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.55,1:37:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There are several cars parked on Steadley Road
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.55,1:37:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and they could be ticketed.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.55,1:37:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're parked on the road
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.55,1:37:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,up here, there is handicapped
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.55,1:37:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can infuse
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.55,1:38:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in our parking lot here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.55,1:38:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't want you to get towed.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.61,1:38:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.00,1:38:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for this opportunity to be here again today.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.00,1:38:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello Susan. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.00,1:38:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.00,1:38:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My question has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.00,1:38:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what you were saying before reminding
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.00,1:38:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,us of the final gate
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.00,1:38:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when the ego dies and that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.00,1:38:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. My question is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.00,1:38:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the, prior to that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.00,1:38:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,event for you,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.06,1:38:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,was the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.06,1:38:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,dying in parts
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.06,1:38:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or might that happen to
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.06,1:38:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,someone else prior to this
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.06,1:38:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,complete death
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.41,1:38:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.41,1:38:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well it's sort of sequential.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.54,1:38:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not facing the final door
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.54,1:38:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,until you've gone through the ones that lead to the final door.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.54,1:38:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But everything else
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.83,1:38:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,being gone and the mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.83,1:38:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.84,1:38:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing left to surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.84,1:39:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You've given control,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.88,1:39:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,survival, you've surrendered all of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.88,1:39:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.88,1:39:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing left to that which
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.88,1:39:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you consider to be yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.88,1:39:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,other than
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.48,1:39:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're down to everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.48,1:39:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You've surrendered everything to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.48,1:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing left except all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.48,1:39:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it dawns on you, life.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.48,1:39:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.93,1:39:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you realize this too must be
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.93,1:39:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,laid down to God once life
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.93,1:39:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,itself, the core of what you believe is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.93,1:39:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,life.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.35,1:39:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings up trepidation.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.60,1:39:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.60,1:39:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.60,1:39:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.11,1:39:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.43,1:39:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of many lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.43,1:39:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,since the beginning of time
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.43,1:39:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,came up.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.97,1:39:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, it was very, very strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.86,1:39:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Overwhelmingly powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.92,1:39:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're surrendering the core
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.92,1:39:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.92,1:40:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which all these lifetimes you believed
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.92,1:40:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the narcissistic core
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.02,1:40:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of your ego, is the source of your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.02,1:40:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you surrender control
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.76,1:40:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,over your life itself to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.76,1:40:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.82,1:40:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it did bring fear and terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.82,1:40:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But having already
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.24,1:40:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,known the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.24,1:40:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so today I've transmitted the same
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.24,1:40:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,frequency to the aura of everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.24,1:40:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When the final doorway appears,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.33,1:40:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,annoyingness, you won't remember from where
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.33,1:40:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or what lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.33,1:40:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But the knowingness comes forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.88,1:40:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that knowingness, you couldn't make the final step.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.88,1:40:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.90,1:40:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.90,1:40:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.41,1:40:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be a certainty,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.41,1:40:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,an absolute certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.41,1:40:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolute certainty is an energy
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.41,1:40:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be sent only by someone
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.41,1:40:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,who's actually lived the reality of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.41,1:41:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't come from the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.51,1:41:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,At that level, the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.67,1:41:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is silent, so you don't have any mind
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.67,1:41:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to refer to anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.68,1:41:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission goes down.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.68,1:41:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same transmission you get in AA,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.68,1:41:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.72,1:41:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Your sponsor is somebody who has authority
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.72,1:41:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and lived through it and done it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.72,1:41:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And it isn't something he read in a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.72,1:41:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, he has
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.72,1:41:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.72,1:41:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's based on
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.72,1:41:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, bitter experience of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.72,1:41:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He learned it the hard way.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.91,1:41:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you give him
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.84,1:41:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the authority that you can
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.84,1:41:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,live your life without a drink,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.84,1:41:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which you don't believe is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.48,1:41:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like one of the
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.86,1:41:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,things that I'm confronting
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.86,1:41:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ego right now is
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.86,1:41:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire for
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.86,1:41:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,approval and
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.86,1:41:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the aversion to
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.86,1:41:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,disapproval or rejection.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.86,1:41:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,See, approval is associated with survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.86,1:42:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In the tribal culture
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.15,1:42:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of the wolf, the dog pack,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.15,1:42:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,without the approval of the pack, you die.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.15,1:42:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So it brings up survival,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.15,1:42:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,really. If you don't have
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.15,1:42:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody else's approval,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.15,1:42:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.15,1:42:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you've got to risk
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.63,1:42:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,death by letting it go.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.16,1:42:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not afraid of dying, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.80,1:42:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Give that one up right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.80,1:42:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.80,1:42:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm more afraid of the disapproval
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.80,1:42:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,than I am death.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.80,1:42:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So then the approval would be
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.80,1:42:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for assurance,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.80,1:42:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for agreement.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.80,1:42:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's pride in a way,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.15,1:42:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.00,1:42:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanting people to like you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.00,1:42:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's coming from lack.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.00,1:42:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need anybody's approval at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.00,1:42:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the less you want their approval,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.00,1:43:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.48,1:43:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to belong to a very elite group.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.48,1:43:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The world didn't know what elite is.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.64,1:43:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you wanted the slightest thing
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.64,1:43:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from any of them, you were automatically out.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.64,1:43:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to be completely
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.86,1:43:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,self-sufficient. If you're looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.86,1:43:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a connection, they just
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.86,1:43:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,got it like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.05,1:43:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you didn't get elected to the club.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.05,1:43:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't want anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.40,1:43:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be total and complete within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.40,1:43:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you have nothing at all,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.78,1:43:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,then the thing is to be content
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.78,1:43:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.39,1:43:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all is a wonderful state.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.39,1:43:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.71,1:43:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has something, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.09,1:43:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To have nothing at all is very hard to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.09,1:43:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Try it. See how hard it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.09,1:43:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody screams and hollers.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.12,1:43:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The family says you've gone insane.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.12,1:43:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Gave it all away, walked away from it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.34,1:43:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He's lost his mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.50,1:43:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.19,1:44:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you can't come from lack.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.19,1:44:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are is already complete and total.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.19,1:44:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't need anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.22,1:44:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It just thinks it does.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.96,1:44:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it thinks it does,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.96,1:44:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that it needs it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.21,1:44:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the feeling you need it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.21,1:44:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is not coming from reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.21,1:44:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just coming from a belief system.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.66,1:44:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you have to have the courage to drop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.04,1:44:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody may say you're stupid
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.04,1:44:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and lost your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.55,1:44:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.04,1:44:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them my doctor says
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.04,1:44:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm perfectly fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.55,1:44:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you folks that are crazy out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.77,1:44:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.77,1:44:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Susan, for this opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.77,1:44:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.77,1:44:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,question about children.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.77,1:44:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's my job
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.77,1:44:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to do the Sunday school at our
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.77,1:44:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Religious Science Church.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.77,1:45:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I usually sign up with the teens.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.77,1:45:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're a little easier for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.77,1:45:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But one time I had the young ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.93,1:45:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we went around the circle,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.93,1:45:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we did some kind of
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.93,1:45:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,affirmation and then someone brought up
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.93,1:45:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and all those suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.93,1:45:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,kids out in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.93,1:45:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, they just brought this thing up
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.93,1:45:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said, and they have what they need too.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.93,1:45:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Also. And then someone said,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.93,1:45:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but I know they don't,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.93,1:45:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I know they don't have what they need.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.93,1:45:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said from truth
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.93,1:45:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that, you know, even death
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.93,1:45:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.25,1:45:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They have what they need until they don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.25,1:45:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I blew a lot of people's
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.25,1:45:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,circuits when I did that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.25,1:45:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you have a way
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.25,1:45:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could relate this truth
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.25,1:45:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to even children
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.25,1:45:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,who may be seeing
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.25,1:45:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or not even children but adults
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.25,1:45:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or anyone who see the appearance
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.25,1:45:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.25,1:45:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you will at that level though.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.25,1:45:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't. I just have to stop doing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.08,1:46:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It kind of falls on deaf ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.08,1:46:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.08,1:46:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I had one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.08,1:46:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I was doing some meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.08,1:46:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I took my glasses
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.08,1:46:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,off and I wasn't thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.08,1:46:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about it at all. Although I do have
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.08,1:46:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this ego desire to not wear these anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.08,1:46:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I was,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.08,1:46:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I put them down at night and I went away,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.08,1:46:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,went to sleep, woke up, took a shower
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.08,1:46:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,came back and said, where's my glasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.08,1:46:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd gone this whole length of time
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.08,1:46:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was okay to not
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.08,1:46:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,wear glasses. And then I got worried
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.08,1:46:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd lost my glasses so I went looking around.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.08,1:46:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where they were from. Last night they were sitting on the table
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.08,1:46:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in the other room. I'd taken them off
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.08,1:46:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said, without thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.08,1:46:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about wanting to heal my
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.08,1:46:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes, I kind of experienced
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.08,1:46:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what it might be like to heal my eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.08,1:46:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for several hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.08,1:46:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it was perfectly okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.08,1:46:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I trick myself into not being attached
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.08,1:46:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to that?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.15,1:46:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.30,1:46:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a very
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.30,1:46:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,focused kind of spiritual practice
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.30,1:47:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender a belief system
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.30,1:47:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and to reaffirm
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.30,1:47:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that my reality is
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.30,1:47:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.30,1:47:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget I had the experience
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.94,1:47:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of out of body a number of times
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.94,1:47:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remember you could see, hear
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.94,1:47:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything was perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.94,1:47:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I realized that
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.94,1:47:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't hear and see
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.94,1:47:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,through the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.94,1:47:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You do it through the etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.94,1:47:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I was seeing from
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.94,1:47:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,up there and the body was down here
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.94,1:47:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's been
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.94,1:47:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,many tests of that
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.94,1:47:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,during surgery and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.94,1:47:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,People could see what's on top of the
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.94,1:47:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,lockers and etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.94,1:47:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were up on the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.94,1:47:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reality
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.94,1:47:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then is the capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.94,1:47:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is not dependent on the physical body
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.94,1:47:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you identify with the physical
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.94,1:47:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,body, then it's limited to the
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.94,1:47:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,physical body's restrictions.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.94,1:47:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you are subject to the physical
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.20,1:47:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,body, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.20,1:47:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'd have to surrender that I am not
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.20,1:48:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,subject to the limitations of my physical body
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.20,1:48:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because my infinite self
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.20,1:48:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with a capital S is not subject
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.20,1:48:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.57,1:48:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What you are is not subject to limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.57,1:48:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only subject to belief system, the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.57,1:48:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.86,1:48:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.86,1:48:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not recommending everybody do what I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.86,1:48:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the edge of the cliff a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.86,1:48:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was willing to
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.37,1:48:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,go over it for the sake of what I was
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.37,1:48:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to achieve. If you go over the cliff,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.24,1:48:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you go over the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.24,1:48:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.24,1:48:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There was that cavalier.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.24,1:48:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question on
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.24,1:48:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the unmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.49,1:48:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Unmanifest?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.49,1:48:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Unmanifest, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.49,1:48:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You said existence arises out
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.49,1:48:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of the unmanifest?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.97,1:48:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence arises
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.97,1:48:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.13,1:48:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the Godhead arises
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.13,1:48:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Godness. Out of Godness arises
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.13,1:48:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,creation. Godhead
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.48,1:48:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is prior to God
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.48,1:49:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the manifestation.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.48,1:49:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Godhead is the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.48,1:49:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.48,1:49:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of everythingness which then
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.86,1:49:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,emerges as the God
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.86,1:49:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.86,1:49:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,arises creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.96,1:49:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.96,1:49:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that if the unmanifest
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.96,1:49:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ultimate state
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.96,1:49:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.96,1:49:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.47,1:49:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.92,1:49:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,neither existent nor non-existent,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.92,1:49:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.40,1:49:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.40,1:49:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence versus non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.40,1:49:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 850.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.40,1:49:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.29,1:49:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a labeling. There's
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.29,1:49:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,neither existence nor non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.29,1:49:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all descriptive
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.29,1:49:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,terminologies.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.32,1:49:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.87,1:49:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond existence or non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.87,1:50:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not subject to existence or non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.87,1:50:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that out of which
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.87,1:50:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,existence arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.89,1:50:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about it yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.89,1:50:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.39,1:50:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a call when you get there.
